{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "baf59226",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 02 - PhoBERT Sentiment & Annotation Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook acts as an execution and inspection runner for the sentiment analysis and article annotation pipeline.\n",
        "\n",
        "Supported flows:\n",
        "1. **Corpus Preparation**: Process raw articles into a normalized training corpus.\n",
        "2. **Manual/File-based Annotation**: Export a stratified review sample for external labeling, and merge it back.\n",
        "3. **LLM Bootstrapping**: Generate labels automatically using either local LLMs (via Ollama) or hosted APIs (via Gemini).\n",
        "4. **PhoBERT Training**: Fine-tune a 3-class Vietnamese PhoBERT sentiment classifier.\n",
        "5. **Inference & Validation**: Run sentiment scoring on the CafeF corpus and validate aggregated outputs."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "1b6faef6",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 0 - Bootstrap"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "94cda49c",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import subprocess\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "IS_KAGGLE = Path('/kaggle').exists()\n",
        "ROOT = Path.cwd().resolve().parent if Path.cwd().name == 'notebooks' else Path.cwd().resolve()\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_command(*args: str, cwd: Path | None = None) -> None:\n",
        "    cmd = [str(arg) for arg in args]\n",
        "    print('$', ' '.join(cmd))\n",
        "    subprocess.run(cmd, cwd=cwd or ROOT, check=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_module(module: str, *args: str) -> None:\n",
        "    run_command(sys.executable, '-m', module, *args)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('IS_KAGGLE:', IS_KAGGLE)\n",
        "print('ROOT     :', ROOT)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "8e812f13",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1 - Runtime Configuration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "91701f3b",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "TRAINING_INPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'training_input.parquet'\n",
        "ANNOTATION_FILE = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'training_annotations.csv'\n",
        "TRAINING_OUTPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'training_corpus.parquet'\n",
        "BOOTSTRAP_OUTPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'training_bootstrap_labels.parquet'\n",
        "MERGED_LABELED_OUTPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'training_labeled.parquet'\n",
        "ANNOTATION_SAMPLE_OUTPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'annotation_sample.csv'\n",
        "MODEL_DIR = ROOT / 'models' / 'phobert-sentiment' / 'latest'\n",
        "CAFEF_ARTICLES = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'processed' / 'articles_clean.parquet'\n",
        "CAFEF_INPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'cafef' / 'cafef_input.parquet'\n",
        "SENTIMENT_OUTPUT = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'processed' / 'article_sentiment_scores.parquet'\n",
        "DAILY_NEWS = ROOT / 'data' / 'main' / 'processed' / 'daily_news_prices.parquet'\n",
        "\n",
        "BASE_MODEL = os.getenv('PHOBERT_BASE_MODEL', 'vinai/phobert-base-v2')\n",
        "BATCH_SIZE = 16\n",
        "MAX_LENGTH = 256\n",
        "EPOCHS = 2\n",
        "LEARNING_RATE = 2e-5\n",
        "SEED = 42\n",
        "\n",
        "# LLM Bootstrapping configurations\n",
        "BOOTSTRAP_BACKEND = 'gemini'  # 'gemini' or 'ollama'\n",
        "BOOTSTRAP_MODEL = 'gemini-2.0-flash'  # e.g., 'gemini-2.0-flash', 'gemma4:latest'\n",
        "CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.8\n",
        "\n",
        "for path in [TRAINING_OUTPUT.parent, MODEL_DIR.parent, SENTIMENT_OUTPUT.parent]:\n",
        "    path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "be40cc1b",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2 - Optional Kaggle Install\n",
        "\n",
        "Use this only when the notebook is running in a fresh Kaggle runtime and the repo dependencies are not installed yet."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "6771e308",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "if IS_KAGGLE:\n",
        "    run_command(sys.executable, '-m', 'pip', 'install', '-q', '-r', 'requirements.txt')\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print('Skipping pip install outside Kaggle.')\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "0d052113",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3 - Prepare A Normalized Training Corpus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "b7eb804f",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.prepare_training_data',\n",
        "    '--input-file', str(TRAINING_INPUT),\n",
        "    '--output-file', str(TRAINING_OUTPUT),\n",
        ")\n",
        "pd.read_parquet(TRAINING_OUTPUT).head(3)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "annotation_options_header",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4 - Annotation Stage\n",
        "\n",
        "Select **either** Option A (Manual labeling) or Option B (LLM bootstrapping) to generate your labeled training dataset."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "option_a_header",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Option A: Manual Annotation Flow\n",
        "\n",
        "Export a random stratified sample, annotate it offline, and merge the annotations file back into the corpus."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "1f406973",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.sample_annotation',\n",
        "    '--input-file', str(TRAINING_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--output-file', str(ANNOTATION_SAMPLE_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--sample-size', '500',\n",
        "    '--seed', str(SEED),\n",
        ")\n",
        "pd.read_csv(ANNOTATION_SAMPLE_OUTPUT).head(3)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "f7d16e11",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.merge_annotations',\n",
        "    '--corpus-file', str(TRAINING_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--annotations-file', str(ANNOTATION_FILE),\n",
        "    '--output-file', str(MERGED_LABELED_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--seed', str(SEED),\n",
        ")\n",
        "pd.read_parquet(MERGED_LABELED_OUTPUT)[['article_id', 'label', 'split']].head(5)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "option_b_header",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Option B: LLM Bootstrapping Flow (with Gemini or Ollama)\n",
        "\n",
        "Uses local or hosted language models to tag expected market-impact sentiment for training corpus articles. Make sure `GEMINI_API_KEY` is present in your environment variables if using `gemini` backend."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "llm_bootstrap_run",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "if BOOTSTRAP_BACKEND == 'gemini':\n",
        "    assert os.getenv('GEMINI_API_KEY'), \"GEMINI_API_KEY environment variable is required for Gemini bootstrapping.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.bootstrap_labels',\n",
        "    '--input-file', str(TRAINING_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--output-file', str(BOOTSTRAP_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--backend', BOOTSTRAP_BACKEND,\n",
        "    '--model', BOOTSTRAP_MODEL,\n",
        "    '--confidence-threshold', str(CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD),\n",
        "    '--limit', '50'  # Remove or increase this limit for the full dataset\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Merge LLM bootstrap annotations back into training corpus splits\n",
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.merge_annotations',\n",
        "    '--corpus-file', str(TRAINING_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--annotations-file', str(BOOTSTRAP_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--output-file', str(MERGED_LABELED_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--confidence-threshold', str(CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD),\n",
        "    '--seed', str(SEED),\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "pd.read_parquet(MERGED_LABELED_OUTPUT)[['article_id', 'label', 'confidence', 'split']].head(5)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "ea068f5e",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5 - Train The Classifier"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "e9f82128",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.train_classifier',\n",
        "    '--labeled-input', str(MERGED_LABELED_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--output-dir', str(MODEL_DIR),\n",
        "    '--base-model', str(BASE_MODEL),\n",
        "    '--epochs', str(EPOCHS),\n",
        "    '--batch-size', str(BATCH_SIZE),\n",
        "    '--learning-rate', str(LEARNING_RATE),\n",
        "    '--max-length', str(MAX_LENGTH),\n",
        "    '--seed', str(SEED),\n",
        ")\n",
        "pd.read_json(MODEL_DIR / 'evaluation.json')\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "f3aba134",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6 - Run CafeF Inference And Validation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "8eb357c0",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "run_module(\n",
        "    'src.sentiment.run_pipeline',\n",
        "    '--mode', 'infer',\n",
        "    '--model-dir', str(MODEL_DIR),\n",
        "    '--cafef-input', str(CAFEF_ARTICLES),\n",
        "    '--cafef-prepared-output', str(CAFEF_INPUT),\n",
        "    '--sentiment-output', str(SENTIMENT_OUTPUT),\n",
        "    '--daily-news-file', str(DAILY_NEWS),\n",
        "    '--batch-size', str(BATCH_SIZE),\n",
        "    '--max-length', str(MAX_LENGTH),\n",
        ")\n",
        "pd.read_parquet(SENTIMENT_OUTPUT).head(5)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "b6e32d71",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7 - Unified E2E Runs (Gemini Support)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "ba8f2833",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "print('--- Unified CLI Commands (Bootstrap via Gemini & Train) ---')\n",
        "print(f\"{sys.executable} -m src.sentiment.run_pipeline \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --mode train \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --training-cafef-input {TRAINING_INPUT} \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --bootstrap-backend gemini \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --bootstrap-model gemini-2.0-flash \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --model-dir {MODEL_DIR}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print('\\n--- Infer Only ---')\n",
        "print(f\"{sys.executable} -m src.sentiment.run_pipeline --mode infer --model-dir {MODEL_DIR}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print('\\n--- E2E Full run (Gemini Bootstrap + PhoBERT Train + Inference) ---')\n",
        "print(f\"{sys.executable} -m src.sentiment.run_pipeline \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --mode full \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --training-cafef-input {TRAINING_INPUT} \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --bootstrap-backend gemini \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --bootstrap-model gemini-2.0-flash \\\\\")\n",
        "print(f\"  --model-dir {MODEL_DIR}\")\n"
      ]
    }
  ],\
